3
00:00:05,473 --> 00:00:10,848
We learned how to enable, disable, expose, and secure actuator endpoints.

4
00:00:10,848 --> 00:00:13,377
We also learned that enabling an endpoint and exposing

5
00:00:13,377 --> 00:00:15,559
an endpoint are two different things.

6
00:00:15,559 --> 00:00:19,253
Enabling an endpoint controls whether it's created and exposing an

7
00:00:19,253 --> 00:00:22,320
endpoint controls whether or not it can be consumed.

8
00:00:22,320 --> 00:00:26,185
We also saw that we can easily secure our actuator endpoints by including the

9
00:00:26,185 --> 00:00:30,096
Spring security library with some optional configuration.

10
